DataElement.preferredName: Total Erythroid Stem Cell Laboratory Procedure Exponent Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The numeric exponent laboratory value of total erythroid stem cells (BFU-E) in a specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Total Erythroid Stem Cell Laboratory Procedure
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Pertaining to an entirety or whole, also constituting the full quantity or extent; complete; derived by addition._Committed, erythroid stem cells derived from myeloid stem cells. The progenitor cells develop in two phases: erythroid burst-forming units (BFU-E) followed by erythroid colony-forming units (CFU-E). BFU-E differentiate into CFU-E on stimulation by erythropoietin, and then further differentiate into erythroblasts when stimulated by other factors. (MeSH)._Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Concepts.definition: Pertaining to an entirety or whole, also constituting the full quantity or extent; complete; derived by addition.
A unipotent hematopoietic progenitor cell derived from myeloid stem cells that is committed to the erythrocyte cell lineage.
